ownedComment.body: Author:Wouter. Created:8/14/04 9:22 PM. Title:. Comment:.
Using a tagged value to link the controller to the activity graph (or use-case).
Testing for proper form field generation, form field inheritance and proper deferring parameters.
should not conflict with the use-cases title property in the resource bundle
A package can only directly hold a single usecase.
checks if a trigger is present when needed
The call executed for a decision point has a void return type.
A decision point's forward is missing a controller call.
In this package we test if different constructions of deferring operations in a use-case produce the expected result.
This method has practically the same name as the use-case, a user reported an error with such construction. This test exists to make sure it does not appear.
The action deferring to this operation has no form field with the same name and type.
This operation exists to test that parameters must have a non-empty name.
wrong type
Exceptions need to be properly forward to the correct resource.
Tests all sorts of messages
This package tests whether or not hyperlink actions are properly rendered.
Page variables need to be properly rendered and taken into account in the forms. Also, they must correctly be imported using a JSP fragment.
Name should be changed to somethings because of pluralization setting.
Each final state should reference the next use-case, this test verifies that.

subvertex.name: anything else (this is not a use-case neither)

ownedComment.body: Final states can hyperlink to the next usecase. They reference use-cases and should create a transition between use-cases this way
tests if the final state hyperlink actually references a use-case, something else is not allowed
testing what happens when the name does not match any use-case name
Final states can carry the name of the next usecase.

Not all tools (such as ARIS) support placing an activity graph inside the namespace of a use-case (since the UML recommends against that), for them we have tagged value that can be place onto the use-case, it will refer to the activity graph.
Tests if a use-case has different actions with the same name, this is not allowed
Tests sending parameters between usecases (the target action form needs to contain the parameters for the originating source action parameters).

mdElement.text: These two hyperlink actions are sharing the same parameter (column)
This table hyperlinkevent contains a parameter that cannot be matched against any table column
This action is rendered using a clickable image.
this type should have been datatype::int
simple collection: treat all columns as objects
The 3rd operation defers without pointing to an actual operation, and this is wrong.
The third operation here is unspecified
This state has more than one outgoing transition
This page is not allowed to defer control
A page is allowed to act as a final state
different order should still be fine
This final state is targetting it's own use-case while at the same time no pages have been modeled, this will surely lead to an infinite loop.
a bad link .. should not be processed as a path
This transition does not need a trigger because it exits an initial state
